goto - The GOTO command allows a batch file to branch to a different location
       to continue executing commands from. To tell the batch file where to 
       go to, a label is placed after the GOTO command. This label must 
       conform to several {guidelines} for it to be a valid batch file 
       label. Syntax : GOTO label

