set - with this command you can set your path, make a "short-cut" for a frase.
      See the examples.

Example(s):
อออออออออออ
SET TEMP=C:\TEMP
SET TMP=C:\TEMP
SET SYSDIR=C:\WINDOWS\SYSTEM

Some default "sets" for windows are:
- for c:\windows\temp --> %temp%
- for c:\windows --> %windir% or %winbootdir% (usually both are working)

Note: With set you can make even a crypted .bat file (this is used by virus
อออออ writers usually).

Example:
ออออออออ
set c=copy
%c% %0 c:\

Cool isn't it ... ? The batch file will copy itself into drive c:\.
The new set, in my case c, will be followed by % like this %c%. Get it ?

Another example for set:
ออออออออออออออออออออออออ
set y=c
set p=o
set o=p
set c=y
%y%%p%%o%%c% c:\autoexec.bat c:\autoexec.bak

Maybe this example helped you understanding the set commands. With "set"
command u can create real "polymorphic" viruses, so keep batch-ing until
u will write yourselve the first .bat virii and make a good article, NOT
as mine. The viruses created with "set" command are crypted, but remember
that to many crypted lines will make windoze to crash the batch file. :(
